array('Type'=>'Zenith','Description'=>'The Zenith completes the Story. It describes the Resolution of the tale, in a comedy the villain is revealed, and everything undone. In a tragedy the hero suffers their painful downfall. In a detective story the vilain is revealed, arrested or killed.'),
array('Type'=>'Logue','Description'=>'A Logue is an Act detached from a Story, it may be a Prologue or an Epilogue. It usually involves direct Narration, but may not. Considered by many an inferior Narrative style.'),
