		$this->AddTable($package,"Integration_Types",$col, 'Type', '', array('Description'=>'How integrated is this Alternate to the Primary? Note: It is quite common when a character first Coalesces a Quantum Alternate that they create an Artefact, Monolith, Real Estate or Province that also draws together the two Quantum universes, with the Descendant having aspects of both worlds, usually including an exit to that universe in the case of Locations. Some Coalesced Characters (usually Solos or Grand-Mercari) can side-step between the worlds of their Alternates (including forwards and backwards in time in the case of Past-lives).','Tooltip'=>'Alternate Types', 'HelpText'=>'Choose an Integration Type for your Alternate', 'Code'=>'Open', 'ContainerPost'=>FALSE, 'DisplayRow'=>'<details data-level="%level%" data-help="%tab-help%" data-tooltip="%tab-tooltip%" ><summary class="it-type">%Type%</summary><p class="it-description">%Description%</p></details>','Template'=>''), array( 
array('Type'=>'Coalesced', 'Description'=>'For the Character these Alternates are essentially merged, becoming one Personality. The new Coalesced Personality may choose whether to retain Personality, Core, or Handicaps from either personality (or any, once they really get going). So the new Personality may replace two of one Handicaps with another Alternate&#39;s Personality and Core. If two Alternates have the same Handicap, Personality or Core, the Values of both may be added to calculate the Character&#39;s Personality Boon so for &quot;Same&quot; Alternates they would double their Personality Value and increase in Boon accordingly. All Coalesced Alternates may add Annexes to the (usually larger) pool of Annexes the Character is currently using. Changing which Annexes are currently available costs an amount of Chi equal to type (e.g. Swapping a Skill slot will cost 2 Chi). All Proficiencies are always available from all Coalesced Alternates. '),
array('Type'=>'Integrated', 'Description'=>'When you have integrated two Personalities they no longer struggle for control, they have worked out how to compromise and work together. They may dream each other&#39;s dreams, blended with their own. Two integrated personalities may swap any (or all) Annexes between each other, lending their abilities from their world to the Alternate in the other. However, the cost must be paid for both (e.g. For the Alternates to swap one of the Talents over would cost 10 Chi, 5 for each). Proficiencies from both Personalities are always available.'),
array('Type'=>'Co-dominant', 'Description'=>'These Alternates are very much separate from each other, but they have worked out how to hand each other control, for a while. Often they will dream dreams of the other life. Handing over control of the body for a given period costs Chi/Sway equal to the duration (e.g. 12 Chi would buy a day). However, either Alternate can initiate the swap back during that time period for free.'),
array('Type'=>'Split', 'Description'=>'These Alternates argue for control over the body. They must keep separate counts of Chi, etc. Wresting control of the body has a cost depending on the situation, these costs are noted in Sway (or Diff)/Chi/Yarn or as modifiers of the same.<br><table class="boon-table"><thead><tr><td>Situation</td><td>Cost in Sway/Chi/Yarn</td></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Normally</td><td>Active Personality Boon x2/ Active Personality Boon/ APB Reduced</td></tr><tr><td>Alternate is trying to wrest back control of their own body</td><td>Halve</td></tr><tr><td>Alternate would gain Chi from Personality or Core</td><td>Halve</td></tr><tr><td>Events would trigger Alternate’s Handicap</td><td>-Twice Handicap Boon/-Handicap Boon/-Handicap Bane points</td></tr></tbody></table><p>So if your body is possessed by a demon with a Personality Boon of 57 when you would gain Chi from your Personality and Core then you can possibly wrest control back with a Personality roll of 14. Card Ordeals can also be used to simulate these contests, with Crippling or greater wounds knocking an Alternate unconscious (such contests are not usually High Stakes, but can be).</p>'),
array('Type'=>'Unstable', 'Description'=>'Even worse than Split, is Unstable, which is basically what happens if you have multiple Split Alternates. For Unstable Characters all Alternates compete to take control, with the winner buying some time based on how much they beat everyone else by. You can run a great game, and tell an amazing story having each Player control a seperate Alternate in an Unstable Character.')));
