		$col=array();
		$col[]=array('Name'=>'Type', 'Type'=>'VARCHAR(16)', 'Edit'=>'<input type="text" value="%s" maxlength="16"/>', 'Display'=>'<span>', 'CSS'=>'twist-use-type', 'Tooltip'=>'Twist Edge');
		$col[]=array('Name'=>'Description', 'Type'=>'MEDIUMTEXT', 'Edit'=>'<textarea>%s</textarea>', 'Display'=>'<p>', 'CSS'=>'twist-use-description', 'Tooltip'=>'How does spending Twists this way affect the world?');
		$col[]=array('Name'=>'Goblin', 'Type'=>'MEDIUMTEXT', 'Edit'=>'<textarea>%s</textarea>', 'Display'=>'<p>', 'CSS'=>'goblin-edge', 'Tooltip'=>'How would this Edge helkp a Goblin?');
		$col[]=array('Name'=>'Demon', 'Type'=>'MEDIUMTEXT', 'Edit'=>'<textarea>%s</textarea>', 'Display'=>'<p>', 'CSS'=>'demon-edge', 'Tooltip'=>'How would this Edge help a Demon?');
		$col[]=array('Name'=>'Dark_Matter', 'Type'=>'MEDIUMTEXT', 'Edit'=>'<textarea>%s</textarea>', 'Display'=>'<p>', 'CSS'=>'dark-matter-edge', 'Tooltip'=>'I want a Dark Matter Sword! How might that work?');
		$col[]=array('Name'=>'Dark_Territory', 'Type'=>'MEDIUMTEXT', 'Edit'=>'<textarea>%s</textarea>', 'Display'=>'<p>', 'CSS'=>'dark-territory-edge', 'Tooltip'=>'If this Edge is in a Location, how bad does that get?');
		
		$this->AddTable($package,'Twists',$col, 'Type', '', array('Description'=>'Twists create abilities in Characters and Descendants that Store them.','Tooltip'=>'Twist Edges', 'HelpText'=>'Choose a Twisted Edge.', 'Code'=>'Open', 'ContainerPost'=>FALSE, 'DisplayRow'=>'<details data-level="%level%" data-help="%tab-help%" data-tooltip="%tab-tooltip%" ><summary class="twist-use-type">%Type%</summary><p class="twist-use-description">%Description%</p><p class="goblin-edge"><strong>Goblin Edge: </strong>%Goblin%</p><p class="demon-edge"><strong>Demon Edge: </strong>%Demon%</p><p class="dark-matter-edge"><strong>Dark Matter Edge: </strong>%Dark_Matter%</p><p class="dark-territory-edge"><strong>Dark Territory Edge: </strong>%Dark_Territory%</p></details>','Template'=>''), array(
array('Type'=>'Possession Pact','Description'=>'Twists can grant the Increated the ability to posess living beings and animate inanimate objects through a Possession Pact. The Target costs the normal Yarn/Twists cost and then the degree of control must also be purchased in Yarn/Twists. It should be noted that Demonic Characters must use Twists for at least one of these costs. Fae characters can achieve the same effects with Yarn alone.', 'Goblin'=>'Goblins have limited abilities to animate objects, but are often adept at creating spasms and shaking in a Target.', 'Demon'=>'Demons are usually fully capable of possessing objects and animating them as bodies.', 'Dark_Matter'=>'By adding a Twist the character’s subconscious mind <q>possesses</q> the Descendant. This isn’t quite the same as a Possession Pact, as the Animated Descendant will act as the Ref decides the character’s subconscious would have it behave. The number of Twists stored in Animate reduced governs the level of Possession Animation that the Descendant has. Animation counts towards a possession pact, automatically. So you can add 1 Twist of your own to increase the possession level from time to time.', 'Dark_Territory'=>'<p>A twisted power that creates possession pacts with plant life, corpses, rocks and props — even people — within the Location. The Possession Pact is limited by the Spending Limit, so that Room 13 (limited to 2) could only Tremble/Shake a Skill Descendant or Vex (Extra). Planet 13 is limited to 21 Twists, it could Supernatural Possess (9) a Daemonlord, Greater Fae or Labyrinthine Bulmäs (7) with 5 Twists left over for additional Targets (<500 in this case).</p><p>Activating the Possession power costs the Dark Territory the smaller of the two costs. So Room 13 would pay 1 Twist and Planet 13 would pay 7 Twists (the additional Targets are not one of the two costs).</p>'),
array('Type'=>'Multiplication','Description'=>'Multiply Sway spent or generated (including any rolled Score) by some amount based on the Twists spent (or stored). Normally you can only use this ability on your own Chi, Pact members spent Chi, or to multiply the effect of any Mercari million-to-one shot. E.g. When Lotho the ‘Penetrations Engineer’ used his Million-to-one shot his slightly Demonic friend Kat doubled the Chi release for 1 Twist.', 'Goblin'=>'All Goblins are capable of doubling their Score or spent Sway for 1 Twist.', 'Demon'=>'Demons are capable of multiplying Sway by 1+Twists spent.', 'Dark_Matter'=>'By storing Twists in the this power the Dark Matter will automatically multiply any Sway spent through, or Score generated by, the the Dark Matter. The Multiplication is equal to 1+ stored Twists double Reduced. However, huge Scores may be difficult to control.', 'Dark_Territory'=>'All Sway spent in the Territory will be automatically doubled.'),
array('Type'=>'Soul Stealing','Description'=>'<p>Soul stealing can only be performed on targets that have entered a Pact with the Demon. Possession and Oppositional pacts do count. Soul-stealing costs a number of Twists equal to the cost for that target. Consult the Sway Table for details of what can be targeted. It is normal to Steal Proficiencies, Annexes and Alternates from a Character for a while.</p><p>Soul stealing in this way is usually only for a limited duration (paid in Sway as you pass each barrier i.e. at the end of the action pay 2 Sway, 4 Sway at the end of the round, 10 Sway at the end of the Combat, and so on), but if the possession target dies or is destroyed before the duration is up then you will keep the stolen goods for free.</p><p>Conversely if you have a Memory stolen you can get it back again by: buying it again, destroying/killing the Character that stole it from you, or you will get it back if they stop paying for it (or get the Chi back if you have brought it again). Anything that is stolen is added to the Character as a Descendant, or as their own Alternate Personality', 'Goblin'=>'Goblins can often steal Thoughts (Proficiencies) from those they encounter, more powerful Goblins may be able to consume Skills and Talents if they can bite or claw the Targe.', 'Demon'=>'Demons are often capable of stealing Alternates from Bulmäs and Mercari.', 'Dark_Matter'=>'By storing Twists in this Edge the Dark Matter will have a Soul Steal power that activates automatically as you strike with the Dark Matter. The Soul Steal automatically affects the target to a level of the stored Twists Reduced.', 'Dark_Territory'=>'<p>Soul Stealing is a gradual process for a Dark Territory. The Targets are limited based on the spending Limit. Spending Limit also governs how long the Target must be in the Dark Territory before the Soul Stealing may affect them (As a Limit Duration). Activating Soul Stealing costs 1 Twist per Target, however it does not pay maintenance costs unless the Target leaves the Dark Territory.</p><p>So Room 13 (Spending Limit 2 Twists) would be capable of Stealing a Skill (1) or Proficiency(1/2) from a Vex (Extra) (1), but would take a year to do it. Planet 13 (Spending limit 21) could steal an Active Personality (7) from most Characters regardless of type or Scale (14) , after only 30 seconds.</p>'),
array('Type'=>'Ignore Facet','Description'=>'Twists spent allow you to ignore all aspects of the specified Facet for a Twist based Duration. A Character or Dark Matter Descendant that is Ignoring a Facet can still generate a score in the Ignored Facet i.e. a Character who is ignoring Rook (and hence Defences) can still generate a score to defend themselves (but they won&#39;t need to versus a Quash attack) or others.', 'Goblin'=>'Spending 1 Twist will allow a Goblin with a Vulnerability Handicap to ignore all aspects of Burden for 1 action (perhaps allowing them to step through a wall of solid rock).', 'Demon'=>'A Demon with a Duty Handicap could spend 7 Twists and ignore Inertia for one Week (so they would not age, starve, suffocate etc in that week either),', 'Dark_Matter'=>'The Dark Matter Descendant Ignores one Facet for each Ignore Facet Edge. However, the Wielder can also Ignore the Facet for a duration calculated from the Stored Twists Reduced.', 'Dark_Territory'=>'The Dark Territory can ignore all aspects of a Facet for a cost of 1 Twist. This ignoring of the Facet has a Duration equal to the Spending Limit of the Dark Territory. This means Room 13 can ignore a Facet for a few minutes, but Planet 13 could ignore a Facet for an Age (~500,000 years). The Dark Territory can extend this power to any targets within the Dark Territory for an additional cost of 1 Twist per target.'),
array('Type'=>'Sway Vampirism','Description'=>'<table class="boon-table"><caption>Sway Vampirism</caption><thead><tr><td>Twists</td><td>Yarn drained</td><td>Actual Sway drained</td></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>1</td><td>1d2</td><td>4-10</td></tr><tr><td>2</td><td>1d4</td><td>4-24</td></tr><tr><td>3</td><td>1d6</td><td>4-42</td></tr><tr><td>4</td><td>1d8</td><td>4-64</td></tr><tr><td>5</td><td>1d10</td><td>4-90</td></tr><tr><td>6</td><td>1d12</td><td>4-119</td></tr><tr><td>7</td><td>2d6</td><td>10-119</td></tr><tr><td>8</td><td>4d3</td><td>24-119</td></tr><tr><td>9</td><td>2d8</td><td>10-194</td></tr><tr><td>10</td><td>1d20</td><td>4-262</td></tr><tr><td>11</td><td>2d10</td><td>5-262</td></tr><tr><td>12</td><td>4d5</td><td>24-262</td></tr><tr><td>13</td><td>2d12</td><td>10-354</td></tr><tr><td>14</td><td>4d6</td><td>24-354</td></tr></tbody></table>', 'Goblin'=>'Sway Vampirism allows Goblins to drain Sway in the form of Chi from those they physically touch.', 'Demon'=>'Sway Vampirism allows the Demon to spend Twists to drain Sway (in the form of Yarn) from a victim, they may pay a Chi cost for Range.', 'Dark_Matter'=>'The Dark Matter Descendant will drain Chi equal to the number of stored Twists each time it affects a target and give them to the Wielder.', 'Dark_Territory'=>'<p>Sway is drained by the Dark Territory at a steady pace. For a Dark Territory the Vampirism cost is calculated in two parts the first is how large the dice used to calculate the drained Sway, the second part is how often it can do that (as a Limit Duration).</p><p>So Room 13 can drain 1d2 Yarn(1) over a year(1). Planet 13 can drain 4d6 Yarn (14) every 5 days (7).</p>'),
array('Type'=>'Twisted Assault','Description'=>'Twists can be used to attack directly. The way the damage is calculated depends on the remaining Stored Twists and the amount being spent. Twisted Assaults can be described as the Player and Ref feel is appropriate, for example you might shoot lasers from your eyes (paying Range costs) or have burning hands. Twisted Assaults usually reflect Nightmare forms and so on (so a Vampire character might claw or bite with her Twisted Assault). <table class="boon-table"><caption>Twisted Assault</caption><thead><tr><th>Twists Spent on Assault</th><th>Assault</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>0</td><td>Play an extra card from your Ordeal Pool during an attack</td></tr><tr><td>1</td><td>Draw and Play one Ordeal card during an attack</td></tr><tr><td>2</td><td>Draw remaining Stored Twists and Play 2 Ordeal Cards during an attack</td></tr><tr><td>3</td><td>Draw remaining Stored Twists and Play 3 Ordeal Cards at any time (including in GRT)</td></tr><tr><td>4</td><td>Draw remaining Stored Twists and Play 3 Ordeal cards as Unsoakable Wounds at any time</td></tr></tbody></table>', 'Goblin'=>'Goblins usually have an Extra card when they attack.', 'Demon'=>'Demons can be capable of intense Power level attacks even when in GRT.', 'Dark_Matter'=>'The Dark Matter Descendant has access to additional Ordeal Cards when used to attack. It can always play an additional card from the Wielder’s Ordeal Pool.', 'Dark_Territory'=>'Dark Territory can always play additional Ordeal Cards from the Pool of anyone within it. '),
array('Type'=>'Twisted Regeneration','Description'=>'<p>Twisted Regeneration is the ability common to most Demons and Goblins that allows them to draw a number of Ordeal cards equal to their current stored Twists Reduced at anytime when they are Wounded. These Ordeal cards may be used to Heal wounds as a normal healing (all wounds lower than the highest healing card and of the same suit are reduced one class).</p><p>Twisted Regeneration can also be activated by paying 1 Twist which will immediately remove all Wounds from the Character, but will increase the Boon of one of their Handicaps by 1. If all available Handicaps are Maxed then the character will gain a &quot;Twisted Regeneration&quot; Boon 1 Descendant that includes a &quot;Scarred&quot; , &quot;Doomed&quot; or similar Handicap of 2.', 'Goblin'=>'Goblins can always heal a few bullet holes and sword slashes.', 'Demon'=>'Demons can appear unstoppable, shedding Wounds easily as they Nightmare Fuel themselves.', 'Dark_Matter'=>'The Dark Matter Descendant can draw Stored Twists Double Reduced additional Ordeal cards whenever damaged to try and heal itself.', 'Dark_Territory'=>'The Dark Territory can draw Stored Twists Double Reduced additional Ordeal cards whenever damaged to try and heal itself.'),
array('Type'=>'Summoning','Description'=>'Twisted Characters can reach beyond reality and call others of their kind. This summoning usually uses the Simple summoning rules, but all costs must be paid in Twists (as though they were Yarn).', 'Goblin'=>'It is not Uncommon for Goblins to use up all their stored Twists summoning more of their kind forth. They may also be accompanied, or acting as Scouts for Increated and Demons.', 'Demon'=>'Demons can easily peel open reality and summon more of their number, however they are not known for their desire to share, and for this reason only has reality not been over run by their ilk.', 'Dark_Matter'=>'It is possible for a Descendant to act as a beacon to Shades, summoning forth Goblins and the like. The Descendant must spend Twists to activate the Summoning ability.', 'Dark_Territory'=>'<p>Dark Territories can create or summon Characters or Descendants into themselves. This is essentially an expression of the Dark territory become more closely aligned with Shades (or one of the Hell/Dungeon Dimensions). Large Dark Territories often have Portals within them to one of these larger Dark Territories through which the summoning takes place (more than Size Boon 45).</p><p>Dark Territories don’t usually make Summoning Rolls (although, if they do, the Easier Summoning rules apply), instead they Summon based on the type Twist cost with an Extend Duration.</p><p>Room 13 can summon Vex (Extras) or Skill Descendants (1) for a Stage of an Ordeal (1). Planet 13 could Summon any sort of Character regardless of Type or Scale (14) for up to 29 days (7).</p>')));
