array('Type'=>'Death-Trap','Description'=>'The way is blocked by a very deadly trap indeed. In the modern Era this may be a landmine or claymore, but more primitive versions include scything blades and sprung spears.'), //ace
array('Type'=>'Snare','Description'=>'Tripwires or snares tangle the feet, and maybe slam down security shutters, blocking the way.'),  //2
array('Type'=>'Toxic-Touch','Description'=>'The door handle /light switch / hand-rail / ladder-rung up ahead has been covered in some poison, perhaps a hallucinogen, an intoxicant, or maybe something deadly.'), //3
array('Type'=>'Pit','Description'=>'Sometimes you don&#39;t need anything more than a big hole in the ground. Maybe with a loose covering of leaves, carpet, or a complex resetting trapdoor.'), //4
array('Type'=>'Gas','Description'=>'Always a favourite with any Villain, gas traps can spray deadly, or knock-out gas as they desire. The way ahead has one.'), //5
array('Type'=>'Blade','Description'=>'Blade traps come in a variety of forms, from cheesewire stretched across a doorway to bamboo spikes in a small hole, all the way up to complex katana-weilding robot arms.'), //6
array('Type'=>'Dead-fall','Description'=>'A dead-fall trap is at its very simplest a rock on the head when you trip the tripwire. The rocks can get very big, and even be complex resetting systems.'), //7
array('Type'=>'Spell-Trap','Description'=>'A spell-trap might be a dangerous curse, a ward to keep out the wrong sort, or something snazzy with lightning bolts and gravity distortions. Or it could just be a bit of superstitious nonsense, like propping a ladder over the route. Have fun with it.'), //9
array('Type'=>'Mechanical','Description'=>'Mechanical traps come in all shapes and sizes, the classic is the crushing walls, or trash compactor, style. These traps usually can be escaped as they have a reset device.'),//9
array('Type'=>'Complex','Description'=>'Complex traps have many components. If you get dropped into a room, the doors lock, and then the room starts to fill with water, you&#39;re in a complex trap. Complex traps have a weakness, usually that they are too complex, and the reset device can be triggered early, but only if you are quick and smart.'), //10
array('Type'=>'Combined','Description'=>'This Obstacle is a combined trap. Draw twice, treat at least one as a Spade.'), //J
array('Type'=>'Beast','Description'=>'A Beast Trap releases or drops Characters into the lare of a beast. Often a (Chorus) Extra Monster, the Beast will at least be a (Vex) Extra.'), //Q
array('Type'=>'Destructive','Description'=>'A Destructive Trap is a one shot trap, it might demolish the buiding, drop all the floors, flood the valley the building is in, destabilize the volcano, or unleash giant rolling balls to chase intruders out and block the exits.'),
