		$this->addHandicap('Unpracticed (Specify)','Sometimes a Character is Fatigued, not by disease or mentally, but simply because they are not very good at what they are trying to do. This is best portrayed by the Unpracticed Handicap. Just remember to Specify what you are unpracticed in. When a Descendant has an Unpracticed Handicap it means the owner cannot get the practice in.',16, 1, 7, true,true,10,1);
		$this->addHandicap('Tiring (Specify)','Tiring Handicaps tire the Character out. This can be useful if using a Descendant should be very tiring... obviously.',16, 1, 8, true,true,10,1);
		$this->addHandicap('Obsolete (Specify)','Sometimes the equipment that you have is a little old, sometimes it needs an update, other times it is completely obsolete. Perhaps it is so old it is actually just a rusted scrap.' ,16, 1, 9, true,true,10,1);
		//Quiet
		$this->addHandicap('Consume (Specific)','This Dependance Handicap means the Character or Descendant must consume something or be wounded. Specify the <q>food</q> that the Handicap requires, such as Zombies having a Consume (Brains) Handicap.',17, 1, 1, true,true,10,1);
		$this->addHandicap('Addicted (Specific)','This Dependance Handicap is meant for those Addictions that are not as terrible as a Consume Handicap, but can still make life very difficult for the Character.',17, 1, 2, true,true,10,1);
		$this->addHandicap('Habit (Specify)','A Habit Handicap is a Dependance upon a behaviour, rather than a substance.',17, 1, 3, true,true,10,1);
		$this->addHandicap('Ambition (Specify)','Ambition Handicaps drive a Character onward and upward. Whether they want to be President, Rich, King, a God or just to get a job, it doesn&#39;t really matter.',17, 1, 4, true,true,10,1);
		$this->addHandicap('Attached (Specify)','Attached Handicaps are used for all those times a Character is stuck with something they shouldn&#39;t be. Maybe they are handcuffed to a suspect, are in a co-dependant relationship, or maybe they are literally the puppet of a greater power.' ,17, 1, 5, true,true,10,1);
		$this->addHandicap('Routine (Specify)','Routine Handicaps are the bane of spontaneous Characters. Some poeple like routine, and it tends to spread. Bureaucracy is a fine example of a Government with a Routine Handicap.',17, 1, 6, true,true,10,1);
		$this->addHandicap('Contingent (Specify)','Contigent Handicaps can stop Characters or Descendants from doing much of anything unless the weather is right, or the public votes a certain way, it always depends on something else, usually uncontrollable and external to the situation at hand.',17, 1, 7, true,true,10,1);
		$this->addHandicap('Craving (Specify)','Craving Handicaps are the way to handle a Descendant or Character that just needs a little something every now and then. It might be batteries, an external powesource, or human souls.',17, 1, 8, true,true,10,1);
		$this->addHandicap('Wasteful (Specify)','Some Descendants are just plain wasteful. You spend hours building them only toi have them explode the first time you use them, or maybe they create more smoke and fumes than actual work whule they operate.' ,17, 1, 9, true,true,10,1);
